trans-unit.source: To register a new user, you must provide his email address, choose a password, and choose a username, which must be unique (you will be notified if another user has already taken that name). The username must include only letters/digits, start with a letter, and be no shorter than 3 characters, nor longer than 50.
trans-unit.target: Per registrare un nuovo utente, devi inserire il suo indirizzo email, una password, e un nome utente, che deve essere unico (sarai avvisato se il nome risulta già registrato). Il nome utente deve includere solo lettere o cifre, iniziare con una lettera, e non essere più corto di 3 caratteri o più lungo di 50.

trans-unit.source: To promote a decent security level, the password must include at least 8 characters, uppercase and lowercase letters, digits, and punctuation (like dashes, stops, parentheses, etc.).
trans-unit.target: Per un sufficiente livello di sicurezza la password deve contare almeno 8 caratteri, incluse maiuscole e minuscole, cifre, e interpunzione (come trattini, punti, parentesi, etc.).

trans-unit.source: Once registered, if messaging is enabled on the server side the user will receive an email message to the email address you specified; he will have to click on the provided link to complete the registration process. Otherwise, you should edit the newly created user and confirm the email registration.
trans-unit.target: Una volta registrato, se questa opzione è abilitata sul server l'utente riceverà un messaggio email all'indirizzo specificato; dovrà quindi cliccare sul link fornito per completare il processo di registrazione. Altrimenti dovrai modificare il nuovo utente e confermare manualmente la registrazione.

trans-unit.source: Filters the first pair so that it must not be after the second pair, at the specified distance from it.
Filters the first pair so that it must be inside the span defined by the second pair, eventually at the specified distance from the container start or end.
Filters the first pair so that it must not be inside the span defined by the second pair, eventually at the specified distance from the container start or end.
Filters the first pair so that its span must overlap the one defined by the second pair, eventually by the specified amount of positions.
Filters the first pair so that its span must not overlap the one defined by the second pair, eventually by the specified amount of positions.
Filters the first pair so that its span must left-align with the one defined by the second pair: A can start with or after B, but not before B.
Filters the first pair so that its span must not left-align with the one defined by the second pair: A can start before B, but not with/after B.
Filters the first pair so that its span must right-align with the one defined by the second pair: A can end with or before B, but not after B.
Filters the first pair so that its span must not right-align with the one defined by the second pair: A can end after B, but not with/before B.
